# FitTrack Pro ETL Pipeline — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a production-grade ETL pipeline using the Medallion Architecture (Bronze/Silver/Gold).
Tech stack: Python 3.10+, DuckDB, Parquet, Pydantic, pandas, httpx, Rich, Streamlit.

## Code Style
- Use type hints on ALL function signatures and return types
- Use snake_case for variables, functions, columns, and file names
- Write docstrings that explain WHAT and WHY (not just HOW)
- Keep functions focused — one responsibility per function
- Prefer explicit over implicit; avoid magic numbers and strings

## Architecture Rules
- All configuration goes in `config/*.yaml` — never hardcode settings in Python
- Use Pydantic models for config validation (`src/utils/config_loader.py`)
- Follow the Medallion pattern: Bronze (raw) → Silver (clean) → Gold (modeled)
- New data sources implement `BaseIngestor` (Strategy pattern) in `src/ingestion/`
- New transforms go in `src/transformation/` (cleaner, transformer, or enricher)
- Quality rules are defined in `config/quality_rules.yaml`, not in code
- The orchestrator (`src/orchestrator.py`) is the only entry point for pipeline runs

## File Organization
- Source code: `src/` (ingestion, transformation, warehouse, quality, monitor, utils)
- Tests: `tests/` — mirror the src/ structure, use pytest fixtures from conftest.py
- Config: `config/` — YAML files for pipeline settings, quality rules, sources
- Data: `data/` — bronze/, silver/, gold/ layers plus sample/ for demo data
- Docs: `docs/` — architecture, guides, glossary

## Testing Conventions
- All tests in `tests/` using pytest
- Shared fixtures in `tests/conftest.py`
- Use `tmp_path` fixture for file operations — never write to real data dirs in tests
- Mock external dependencies (APIs, file system) with pytest-mock
- Test naming: `test_<what>_<condition>_<expected>` (e.g., `test_cleaner_removes_duplicates`)

## Data Conventions
- Parquet for all intermediate storage (Bronze and Silver layers)
- DuckDB for the Gold analytical warehouse
- Metadata columns prefixed with `_` (e.g., `_ingested_at`, `_source_name`)
- Quality scores range 0-100, gate threshold is 50

## When Generating Code
- Import from `src.*` using absolute imports
- Log with `get_logger(__name__)` from `src.utils.logger`
- Handle errors gracefully — log the error, don't crash the pipeline
- Use `Path` objects (not string paths) for file operations
- Add new dependencies to `pyproject.toml`, not requirements.txt

## Do NOT
- Create new files when editing existing ones would work
- Add dependencies without checking if an existing one covers the need
- Write to `data/bronze/`, `data/silver/`, or `data/gold/` in tests
- Hardcode file paths, API URLs, or thresholds — use config
- Skip type hints or docstrings on public functions
